1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,110
Win rate is a lagging indicator.

2
00:00:02,510 --> 00:00:03,520
It tells you what happened.

3
00:00:03,730 --> 00:00:04,370
Not why.

4
00:00:04,900 --> 00:00:07,220
Most GTM teams track win rate as a

5
00:00:07,270 --> 00:00:08,120
performance metric.

6
00:00:08,750 --> 00:00:11,110
But win rate without context is noise.

7
00:00:11,810 --> 00:00:13,150
Did you win because your product was

8
00:00:13,210 --> 00:00:13,500
better?

9
00:00:14,010 --> 00:00:15,530
Because your champion had authority?

10
00:00:16,310 --> 00:00:17,900
Because the competitor made a mistake?

11
00:00:18,710 --> 00:00:20,350
Because your rep happened to ask the

12
00:00:20,410 --> 00:00:21,120
right question?

13
00:00:21,850 --> 00:00:22,730
You do not know.

14
00:00:23,010 --> 00:00:25,210
And if you do not know why you win, you

15
00:00:25,280 --> 00:00:26,320
cannot replicate it.

16
00:00:26,950 --> 00:00:29,640
AI changes this by analyzing what

17
00:00:29,700 --> 00:00:31,780
actually happened in the deals you won.

18
00:00:32,470 --> 00:00:34,280
Which discovery questions were asked.

19
00:00:34,810 --> 00:00:36,450
Which objections came up and how they

20
00:00:36,480 --> 00:00:37,020
were handled.

21
00:00:37,430 --> 00:00:39,020
Which stakeholders were engaged and

22
00:00:39,110 --> 00:00:39,380
when.

23
00:00:40,050 --> 00:00:42,080
Win rate becomes a starting point.

24
00:00:42,650 --> 00:00:44,690
The pattern behind the win rate becomes

25
00:00:44,740 --> 00:00:45,430
the strategy.

26
00:00:46,240 --> 00:00:47,660
That is how you build a repeatable

27
00:00:47,710 --> 00:00:48,400
revenue motion.

28
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:50,100
Follow A-Gent to build it.
